.TH MARKBACK 1 "March 2026" "version 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
markback \- scheduled pull-based backup manager for home network services
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B markback
.I command
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B markback
is a backup daemon and CLI for pulling backups from home network services.
It supports two backup providers: Home Assistant API backups (WebSocket-based
listing/downloading, REST for triggering, signed URLs for download) and SSH/SCP
file transfers. Backups are scheduled via cron expressions and managed with
configurable retention policies.
.PP
The daemon runs as a macOS launchd service. Secrets (API tokens, SSH keys)
stored as
.B op://
references are resolved via the 1Password CLI and cached in the platform
keychain (macOS Keychain, Linux secret-tool, Windows cmdkey) using the
.B auth
command, so the daemon runs without requiring 1Password to be unlocked.
SSH configuration is read from
.I ~/.ssh/config
for Host aliases, Hostname, Port, User, and IdentityAgent.
.PP
Configuration is stored in
.I ~/.config/markback/config.yaml
as YAML.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Create a default configuration file at
.IR ~/.config/markback/config.yaml .
Will not overwrite an existing file.
.TP
.B auth
Resolve all
.B op://
secret references in the configuration (API tokens, SSH keys) via the
1Password CLI and cache the resolved values in the platform keychain.
Run this once after changing secrets, before starting the daemon.
.TP
.B auth \-\-clear
Remove all cached secrets from the platform keychain.
.TP
.B daemon
Run the backup scheduler in the foreground. This is the command invoked
by launchd. Schedules all configured backups according to their cron
expressions and runs until interrupted (SIGINT or SIGTERM).
.TP
.B run \fR[\fIname\fR]
Manually trigger a backup. If
.I name
is provided, only that backup job runs. Otherwise, all configured jobs run.
.TP
.B now
Run all configured backups immediately, ignoring schedules. Equivalent to
.BR "markback run" .
.TP
.B dry-run \fR[\fIname\fR]
Simulate backups without transferring files. Connects to each target to
verify connectivity and configuration. For SSH targets, checks that the
remote file exists. For HA API targets, verifies authentication and lists
existing backups on the server. Prints a summary table of results.
.TP
.B list
Display a table of all configured backup jobs showing name, type, folder,
schedule, and retention count.
.TP
.B status
Show recent backup history from the status log, including timestamps,
file sizes, and success/failure status. Displays the most recent 20 entries.
.TP
.B version\fR, \fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.B help\fR, \fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses YAML format with two top-level keys:
.TP
.B storage.base_dir
Base directory for all backup files. Supports
.B ~/
expansion.
.TP
.B storage.log_file
Path to the application log file. Supports
.B ~/
expansion.
.TP
.B backups
A list of backup job definitions. Each job supports these fields:
.RS
.TP
.B name
Unique identifier for this backup job (required).
.TP
.B type
Provider type:
.B ha_api
or
.B ssh
(required).
.TP
.B schedule
Cron expression for when to run (required).
.TP
.B folder
Subdirectory within base_dir for this job's files. Defaults to
.BR name .
.TP
.B filename
Output filename template with Go time format in braces, e.g.
.BR "pihole_backup_{2006-01-02}.zip" .
If omitted, uses
.IR name-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.ext .
.TP
.B retention
Number of backup files to keep. Oldest are deleted first. Default: 4.
.RE
.PP
For
.B ha_api
type, additionally:
.RS
.TP
.B ha_url
Home Assistant base URL (required).
.TP
.B ha_token
Long-lived access token. Supports
.B op://
references for 1Password CLI resolution (required).
.RE
.PP
For
.B ssh
type, additionally:
.RS
.TP
.B host
SSH hostname or alias (required).
.TP
.B user
SSH username (required).
.TP
.B remote_path
Path to the file to download (required unless
.B remote_pattern
is set).
.TP
.B remote_pattern
Glob pattern to find the newest matching file on the remote host (alternative
to
.BR remote_path ).
For example,
.BR "/home/pi/backups/unbound/unbound-*.tar.gz" .
.TP
.B ssh_key
SSH private key for this backup job. Supports
.B op://
references to retrieve keys from 1Password (PKCS#8 format supported).
If omitted, the SSH agent or
.I ~/.ssh/config
IdentityAgent is used.
.TP
.B pre_command
Command to run on the remote host before downloading.
.TP
.B post_command
Command to run on the remote host after downloading.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B markback init
Create a default configuration file with example backup targets.
.TP
.B markback auth
Resolve 1Password secrets and cache them in the system keychain.
.TP
.B markback auth \-\-clear
Remove all cached secrets from the system keychain.
.TP
.B markback dry-run
Verify connectivity and configuration for all targets without transferring files.
.TP
.B markback dry-run pihole
Test only the pihole backup configuration.
.TP
.B markback run pihole
Manually trigger the pihole backup.
.TP
.B markback now
Run all backups immediately.
.TP
.B markback list
Show all configured backup jobs.
.TP
.B markback status
Show recent backup results.
.TP
.B markback version
Print version information.
.SH SERVICE MANAGEMENT
To install as a macOS launchd service:
.PP
.RS
.B launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.markback.daemon.plist
.RE
.PP
To stop the service:
.PP
.RS
.B launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.markback.daemon.plist
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (backup failure, configuration error, or connectivity issue).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/markback/config.yaml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/Library/Logs/markback.log
Default log file location.
.TP
.I ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.markback.daemon.plist
launchd service definition.
